comments: Aldridge (BKN) slightly extends his leg out as he establishes himself in a screening position in Jones Jr.'s (CHI) path, and marginal contact occurs on the screen.
DeRozan (CHI) jumps away from Brown (BKN) while bringing his arm into a vertical position and any contact is deemed incidental during the play at the basket.

Brown (BKN) extends his arm out to pursue the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Ball's (CHI) head during the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Harden's (BKN) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Aldridge (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by LaVine (CHI).
Vucevic (CHI) moves alongside of and absorbs the marginal contact created by Aldridge (BKN) at the end of the drive.
Brown (BKN) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Aldridge (BKN) could be deemed to be in the lane for about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
DeRozan (CHI) brings his arm down and makes contact with Brown's (BKN) arm, which affects his shot near the rim.
Brown (BKN) jumps foward and makes contact with LaVine's (CHI) body, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Aldridge's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together on the cut down the lane.
Aldridge (BKN) is firming up when he absorbs the body contact with Jones Jr. (CHI) during the off ball screen.
During the screen, Durant (BKN) and Jones Jr. (CHI) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Jones Jr. (CHI) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Harden (BKN) cleanly dislodges the ball from DeRozan (CHI) and DeRozan legally recovers the loose ball in the back court.
Harden (BKN) slightly extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs with DeRozan's (CHI) body, which does not affect his ability to stay on his intended path during the drive.
During the inbound, Jones Jr. (CHI) has a resting hand on Durant's (BKN) back and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his FOM.
Durant (BKN) hooks Jones Jr. (CHI) at the start of his drive and the contact dislodges him from his legal guarding position.
Jones Jr. (CHI) trails Durant (BKN) and incidental foot to foot contact occurs as they come around the screen.
Durant (BKN) commits a take foul on Dosunmu (CHI).
Dosunmu (CHI) legally contests Mills' (BKN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Thomas (BKN) gathers the ball on two feet and establishes his left foot as his pivot foot, he then lifts and re-plants prior to his shot attempt.
DeRozan (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during Thomas' (BKN) jump shot attempt.
